<P>
SEOUL JAILS 2 IN TRIP PROBE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Korean authorities jailed two dissident leaders and questioned others 
about an illegal trip to Communist North Korea by a colleague, the Rev. Moon Ik 
Hwan, police reported. Opponents accused the government of using Moon's trip 
last week as an excuse to crack down on dissent, and students supporting him 
battled police in seven cities. Dissidents have sought their own contact with 
North Korea on the subject of reunification, but the government insists that 
all dialogue be handled through official channels. Meanwhile, Moon was reported 
on his way to Beijing and planning to return home by way of Japan later in the 
week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
