<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Northwest May Stay in St. Paul: Minnesota Atty. Gen. Hubert H. Humphrey III 
said John Davis, son of millionaire Marvin Davis, assured him that his father 
would keep Northwest Airlines' operations in St. Paul and expand the airline if 
Davis' $90-a-share bid for the airline is accepted. Minnesota officials have 
vowed to fight any effort to break up the airline. Meanwhile, NWA said it 
reached a contract agreement with 10,500 clerical workers and reservation and 
ticket agents. 
</P>
