<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pickens Buys Japanese Shares: Corporate raider T. Boone Pickens Jr. has become 
the largest shareholder of Koito Manufacturing Co., a leading auto parts 
supplier closely affiliated with Toyota Motor Corp., securities industry 
sources said in Tokyo. It's thought to be the first time a U.S. raider has made 
a major investment in a Japanese-listed company, sources said. Pickens appears 
to have purchased 20% of the outstanding common shares of Koito from Azabu 
Jidosha, a prominent real estate speculator, the sources said. The purchase 
made Toyota, with a 19% interest, the firm's second-largest shareholder, they 
said. Koito's share price has been rising in recent months, apparently because 
of Pickens' purchases, sources said. 
</P>
