<HEADLINE>
<P>
ISRAELI PAPER QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TEL AVIV 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An English-language Israeli daily newspaper, the Nation, ceased publication 
Monday, seven months after it was launched to challenge the 56-year-old 
Jerusalem Post for an estimated 100,000 native English speakers. 
</P>
<P>
Editor and Managing Director Hesh Kestin said directors will reorganize and 
refinance the Nation, which has suffered from high employee turnover since its 
September launching. 
</P>
</TEXT>
