opponents. But Sunday night, it didn't compare to the task of NBA official Ron 
Olesiak, who tries pull the Laker center away from a first-quarter, 
bench-clearing battle that began when Buck forward Larry Krystkowiak apparently 
struck Abdul-Jabbar in the forehead. Krystkowiak was called for the foul, but 
Abdul-Jabbar came away with a technical foul after retaliating as Olesiak and 
Laker forward A.C. Green tried to separate the two combatants. In his way, 
Abdul-Jabbar had the last word: the Lakers won, 118-117. KIRK McKOY / Los 
