VALLEY EARNINGS: SIERRACIN REPORTS PROFIT DOUBLED IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sierracin Corp. in Sylmar said that its fourth-quarter profit more than doubled 
from a year earlier and that its full-year 1988 earnings rose 54%. 
</P>
<P>
The company, which principally builds cockpit windows and other equipment for 
the aircraft industry, said profit for the quarter that ended Dec. 31 climbed 
to $1.22 million from $530,000, and revenue rose to $21.1 million from $17.9 
million. 
</P>
<P>
Sierracin said its quarterly profit would have been higher had it not been for 
cost overruns on certain contracts and other operating cost increases. 
</P>
<P>
For the full year, Sierracin's net income rose to $3.12 million from $2.03 
million, and its annual revenue increased to $82.7 million from $72.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
Last week, company Chairman Christoph Tribble and some other executives said 
they were considering making an offer to buy the company. 
</P>
