<P>
IMELDA TO EMBALM, DISPLAY MARCOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ousted former Philippine President Ferdinand E. Marcos will be embalmed and 
preserved for display in Hawaii if he dies in exile, his wife, Imelda, said in 
an interview published today. 
</P>
<P>
She told the Manila daily Business World she would make a deliberate spectacle 
of her husband if the government of President Corazon Aquino refuses to allow a 
Philippine burial. 
</P>
<P>
"I'll keep Marcos here (in Hawaii) until 1992. Then I'll bring him home. My 
mother-in-law is also waiting to be buried," she said. Marcos's mother died 
last May and was embalmed so that her son could attend her burial. 
</P>
<P>
"Ferdinand does not wish to be buried (in the United States)," Imelda Marcos 
said. "If he is to be cremated after 1992, then his wish is for his ashes to be 
scattered across the Philippines to fertilize his country." 
</P>
