<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ASTROS SIGN SCOTT TO ANOTHER 2 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Houston Astros have signed 1986 Cy Young Award winner Mike Scott to a 
two-year contract extension worth a guaranteed $3.925 million. 
</P>
<P>
Scott, who will earn $1.3 million in 1989, the final year of a two-year 
contract, will have a base salary of $1.95 million in 1990 and 1991. He will 
also get a $25,000 signing bonus, according to terms agreed upon Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Scott will make an additional $450,000 if he pitches 205 innings or makes 32 
starts in each of the 1989 and 1990 seasons. The contract contains additional 
bonuses for making the All-Star team and for finishing first, second or third 
in Cy Young Award voting. If he earns all available bonuses, Scott would earn 
$5.125 million during the extension. 
</P>
<P>
Scott has a 66-39 record over the past four seasons since developing the 
split-fingered fastball that allowed him to lead the majors in 1986 with 306 
strikeouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Mike Scott 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
